  "prompt": "What is vector design?",
  "response": "Vector design is a graphic design technique that uses mathematical formulas to create scalable images composed of points, lines, and curves. Here are key characteristics:\n\n1. Key Features:\n- Mathematically defined graphics\n- Can be scaled infinitely without losing quality\n- Precise and sharp at any size\n- Created using vector design software\n\n2. Common Software\n- Adobe Illustrator\n- CorelDRAW\n- Inkscape\n- Affinity Designer\n\n3. Primary Uses\n- Logos\n- Icons\n- Illustrations\n- Infographics\n- Technical drawings\n- Typography\n- Web graphics\n\n4. Advantages\n- Resolution-independent\n- Small file sizes\n- Easy to edit and manipulate\n- Precise control over design elements\n\n5. Creation Process\n- Uses geometric shapes\n- Manipulates anchor points\n- Applies mathematical algorithms\n- Adjusts curves and lines\n\n6. Contrast with Raster Design\n- Raster uses pixels\n- Vector uses mathematical paths\n- Vector maintains quality when resized\n- Raster becomes pixelated when enlarged\n\n7. Common Applications\n- Branding\n- Graphic design\n- Digital and print media\n- Animation\n- Digital art\n\nVector design offers high flexibility and professional-quality graphic creation.",
